@width 80
@index index
@node main "MAXs BBS chat door and pager"

@{B}Chat door and pager by R. Smith.@{UB}

        @{"Chat door" link chat}
        @{"Pager" link pager}
	@{"Contact" link cont}
	@{"History" link hist}
	@{"Copyright" link copy}
@endnode
@node chat "The chat door.."

You can use this one separately from the pager if you want, Its just a
chat door. Just remember to set sensible access...

Apart from writing on the split screen, you can use some other key
combinations for certain functions.

These are:
		  CTRL-C Clear window
		* CTRL-D Raw Downloads
		* CTRL-G Goodbye (friendly logout user)
		* CTRL-S User Shell (not available yet)
		* CTRL-U Raw Uploads
		* ESC    Quit back.

		*Local only

Certain other characters and key combinations are filtered out for various
reasons as well.

Other than that, you just type.
@endnode
@node pager "The paging door.."

This door will ask for a reason for paging, and then interrupt the local
user with a paging window on the Workbench screen. The title will have
the user's name, and their message will be underneath. A few beeps will
be played to alert you to this. The user's @{B}*Name*@{UB} will be
highlighted.

There are a few settings you can change in @{B}pager.cfg@{UB}, please
refer to that file for information. It is commented.

One thing to note however is that the pager will try to run the chat
door if its window is closed. The chat door you use would have to be
compatible with this. If you do not want to run the door direct, just
edit the config file so that the door will not be found.
@endnode
